VStudents shine
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe Annamacharya keertana competitions conducted by the Vijayawada Cultural Academy at G.V.R. Government College of Music and Dance attracted a large number of entries from juniors (5 to 15 years of age) and seniors (16 to 18 years of age).Speaking on the occasion, secretary of the Cultural Academy Seeram Subramanyam said that the competitions were being conducted to mark the 89th Jayanthi of late Mallik, a fine musician and composer, whose tunes for Annamacharya keertanas composed five decades ago were still popular.Mallik served as composer in the Akashvani Kendras at Chennai and Vijayawada for nearly five decades.Among Mallik&#8217;s compositions were all-time hits likeAdigo Alladigo Sriharivasamu... (Madhyamavathi),Tandanana Bhala Tandanana... (Bauli).Vocal vidwan Modumudi Sudhakar, a staffer of the Vijayawada Akashvani, was the judge for both junior and senior categories.The cash awards (Rs. 1,000 for first prize winners and Rs. 500 for second prize winners) will be awarded on August 21 at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram, declared the secretary S. Subramanyam.Some of the attractive Annamacharya keertanas that were rendered by students in the competitions wereMuddugare Yasoda...,Jagadapu Chanuvula... andPidikita Talambraluamong others.
